\begin_layout Standard
We will be working with a weighted inner product.
 It takes two functions and returns the integration of their multiplication with the weight function over a certain predefined interval 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

.
 Square root of an inner product of the same function twice is called a norm.
 Normalized polynomials will then be polynomials that have their norm equal to one.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
